<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911217-0108</DOCNO><DOCID>911217-0108.</DOCID><HL>   REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:   The New Founders</HL><DATE>12/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A20</SO><GV>EXECUTIVE (EXE)</GV><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Speaking at the home of James Madison yesterday tocommemorate the ratification of the Bill of Rights, PresidentBush said, &quot;I simply cannot believe that the Framersenvisioned that the central government would spend a quarterof the gross national product of this country.&quot; While U.S.liberals now laugh at such sentiments, it's worth noting thatdozens of finance and justice ministers from emergingdemocratic nations attended the Madison ceremony. It's verylikely that many of them will strive to shape their nationsin line with the American Founders' original vision of alimited government.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>